    </sec>
    <sec id="SEC3.5">
      <title>3.5 Extend</title>
      <p>The <italic>extend</italic> step receives alignments that passed the <italic>filter</italic> step. It is computed using a traditional banded NW algorithm. Significant alignments are then printed with their full description. It should be noted that if the <italic>filter</italic> step provides good efficiency, no optimization of the <italic>extend</italic> step is required. Indeed, if most false positive alignments have already been ruled out, the <italic>extend</italic> step should only take a negligible fraction of the total execution time.</p>
    </sec>
